data[0][text]: 1. How often do you have difficulty concentrating on what people are saying to you even when they are speaking to you directly?
data[10][text]: 11. How often do you fidget or squirm with your hands or feet when you have to sit down for a long time?
data[11][text]: 12. How often do you feel overly active and compelled to do things, like you were driven by a motor?
data[12][text]: 13. How often do you make careless mistakes when you have to work on a boring or difficult project?
data[13][text]: 14. How often do you have difficulty keeping your attention when you are doing boring or repetitive work?
data[14][text]: 15. How often do you misplace or have difficulty finding things at home or at work?
data[15][text]: 16. How often are you distracted by activity or noise around you?
data[16][text]: 17. How often do you feel restless or fidgety?
data[17][text]: 18. How often do you find yourself talking too much when you are in social situations?
data[18][text]: 19. How often do you have difficulty waiting your turn in situations when turn taking is required?
data[19][text]: 20. How often do you interrupt others when they are busy?
data[1][text]: 2. How often do you leave your seat in meetings or other situations in which you are expected to remain seated?
data[2][text]: 3. How often do you have difficulty unwinding and relaxing when you have time to yourself?
data[3][text]: 4. When you're in a conversation, how often do you find yourself finishing the sentences of the people you are talking to before they can finish them themselves?
data[4][text]: 5. How often do you put things off until the last minute?
data[5][text]: 6. How often do you depend on others to keep your life in order and attend to details?
data[6][text]: 7. How often do you have trouble wrapping up the final details of a project, once the challenging parts have been done?
data[7][text]: 8. How often do you have difficulty getting things in order when you have to do a task that requires organization?
data[8][text]: 9. How often do you have problems remembering appointments or obligations?
data[9][text]: 10. When you have a task that requires a lot of thought, how often do you avoid or delay getting started?
